keywords:
  - transcriptomics
  - feature selection
  - time-series
  - biomarker discovery
  - stability selection
  - machine learning
  - bioinformatics
abstract: >-
  METI-FS is a computational framework for sparse biomarker discovery
  from time-series transcriptomics data. It integrates differential expression,
  temporal trend analysis, co-expression networks, machine-learning stability
  selection with gap-union thresholding, and protein-protein interaction
  evidence into a unified pipeline.
